    "Reviewers can focus on the research as it stands, without having to comment on its fit for a particular journal.",
    "Open dialog may encourage reviewers to be more collegial and constructive.",
    "Authors could use the opportunity offered by preprint review to publicly respond to questions and concerns, thereby ensuring that their responses can be read by all.",
    "Finally, by making the comments of reviewers an integral element of scholarly discourse, peer review will increasingly be seen as a scholarly contribution in its own right.",
    "Despite the benefits noted above, preprint review is not without potential challenges."
